page.title: 08Housing in north W.Wittering
page.content: There are 4 groups of houses in this area, with 11 widely spaced houses along the main road, 4 in Ellanore Lane, 1 in Rookwood,and 1 in Sheepwash Lane,all in big gardens. Rookwood, on the coast, is an estate of 10 houses or bungalows set in large grounds; Chapel and Redlands Lanes each have 8 one being moated. Malthouse Cottages on the E.side of the main road, were Council built though a number have now been bought by tenants.There are 36 semi-detached houses with small gardens. There are no garages but 18 have parking space on a slip road. The area has laid on water and electricity. Oil is usually used for heating. There is no gas. Only Malt- house Cottages and the 3 houses opposite have main drainage the rest have cesspits or septic tanks.
